# Staging VM Rebuild — {{PROJECT}}

Full from-zero runbook to bring up the staging environment on a fresh VM.
Run this once when provisioning a new staging server, and again if the VM is rebuilt.

## Server

{{#VPS}}- Host: `{{STAGING_SSH_HOST}}`
- User: `{{STAGING_SSH_USER}}`
- SSH: `ssh -i {{STAGING_SSH_KEY_PATH}} {{STAGING_SSH_USER}}@{{STAGING_SSH_HOST}}`
{{/VPS}}{{#GCP}}- VM: `{{STAGING_VM_NAME}}` (zone `{{GCP_ZONE}}`, project `{{GCP_PROJECT}}`)
- SSH: `gcloud compute ssh {{STAGING_VM_NAME}} --zone={{GCP_ZONE}} --tunnel-through-iap`
{{/GCP}}
- Deploy dir on host: `/opt/{{PROJECT}}-deployment/` (clone this repo there)
- External URL: `https://{{STAGING_DOMAIN}}`

## Prerequisites on the VM

```bash
# Docker + Compose plugin
curl -fsSL https://get.docker.com | sudo sh
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER       # log out + back in for group change

# Caddy for TLS termination
sudo apt install -y caddy

# Git
sudo apt install -y git
```

## Steps

### 1. Clone the deployment repo

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /opt/{{PROJECT}}-deployment
sudo chown $USER:$USER /opt/{{PROJECT}}-deployment
cd /opt
git clone <your-repo-url> {{PROJECT}}-deployment
cd {{PROJECT}}-deployment
```

### 2. Create the external network

The app stack and (future) logging stack share this network from separate compose files.

```bash
sudo docker network create {{PROJECT}}-network
```

### 3. Upload env files from your workstation

env files are gitignored; you upload them out-of-band.

{{#VPS}}```bash
scp -i {{STAGING_SSH_KEY_PATH}} \
  staging/env/{{PROJECT}}-core.env staging/env/user-service.env \
  {{STAGING_SSH_USER}}@{{STAGING_SSH_HOST}}:/opt/{{PROJECT}}-deployment/staging/env/
```
{{/VPS}}{{#GCP}}```powershell
gcloud compute scp --tunnel-through-iap --zone={{GCP_ZONE}} `
  .\staging\env\{{PROJECT}}-core.env .\staging\env\user-service.env `
  {{STAGING_VM_NAME}}:/opt/{{PROJECT}}-deployment/staging/env/
```
{{/GCP}}

### 4. Configure host-level Caddy for TLS

The internal nginx binds to `127.0.0.1:3030`. Caddy on the host terminates TLS and reverse-proxies.

Edit `/etc/caddy/Caddyfile`:

```
{{STAGING_DOMAIN}} {
    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:3030
}
{{#WEB_ADMIN}}
admin-{{STAGING_DOMAIN}} {
    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:3031
}
{{/WEB_ADMIN}}
```

Reload:
```bash
sudo systemctl reload caddy
```

### 5. Start the stack

```bash
sudo docker compose -f staging/docker-compose.yml up -d
```

Pull latest images and roll forward later with:
```bash
sudo docker compose -f staging/docker-compose.yml pull && \
sudo docker compose -f staging/docker-compose.yml up -d
```

### 6. Smoke check

```bash
curl https://{{STAGING_DOMAIN}}/health   # should return 200 OK
```

## Auto-deploy via GitHub Actions

After this is up, the workflow at `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` (in `{{PROJECT}}-core`) auto-deploys on every push to `dev`. Set these secrets per code repo:

{{#VPS}}- `SSH_HOST` = `{{STAGING_SSH_HOST}}`
- `SSH_USER` = `{{STAGING_SSH_USER}}`
- `SSH_PRIVATE_KEY` = contents of `{{STAGING_SSH_KEY_PATH}}` (private half)
- `DOCKERHUB_USERNAME`, `DOCKERHUB_TOKEN` (if pushing to DockerHub)
{{/VPS}}{{#GCP}}- `GCP_SA_KEY` = service-account JSON with Compute IAP Tunnel User + Artifact Registry Writer
- `STAGING_VM_NAME` = `{{STAGING_VM_NAME}}`
- `GCP_ZONE` = `{{GCP_ZONE}}`
{{/GCP}}

## Production rebuild

Production setup is deferred at bootstrap. When ready to publish, run `/configure-prod` from the workspace root to fill in the `prod/` skeleton, then follow `prod/REBUILD.md` (created by that skill).
